Astrakhan Communists call for revolution | WATERMELON
November 7th

05 Nov 2019, 13:45


Society
Main





The Astrakhan branch of the Communist Party invites residents of the entire Astrakhan region to public events dedicated to the 102nd anniversary of the Great October Socialist Revolution.

Astrakhan Communists urge to go out under the slogan "Defend the social gains of October!" They recall that it was the October Revolution that gave our country such social rights as: universal women's suffrage, an 8-hour working day, paid leave, paid maternity leave, free vocational and early childhood education, free medicine, free spa treatment and free housing . "All this is the first time in the world, more than this was not in any country!", The Communist Party said in a statement.
The Communists published a map of events held on November 7, which include:
- the city of Astrakhan: a meeting on the square to them. Lenin at 12:30;
- Akhtubinsk city: a meeting on the square to them. Lenin at 10:00 and a concert in the Akhtuba district center of culture at 17:00;
- village Enotaevka: laying flowers in the square to them. Lenin at 10:00;
- Liman village: laying flowers at the monument to Lenin (village administration) at 10:00;
- Kamyzyak city: rally at the monument to Lenin (House of Culture) at 10:00;
- Kharabali city: laying flowers at the square to them. Lenin at 10:00;
- the city of Znamensk: laying flowers on the square to them. Lenin at 08:30;
- the village of Ikryanoye: a rally in the central square to them. Lenin at 10:00;
- the village of Krasny Yar: laying flowers in the park of the 50th anniversary of Victory (at the monument to Lenin) at 10:00.
Earlier on the Telegram channel, Aitov Halit said: “The authorities refused us a traditional march on November 7 in places where the Victory Day parade, May Day demonstration, religious procession, etc. are held annually. Due to the fact that processions along these routes are prohibited. ”
November 5, 2019 17:45
